    <summary>Bambu Farm Manager Server is the always-on local backend for managing multiple Bambu printers on a LAN. It coordinates device communication, central job queues, and dispatch to keep print farms running reliably after initial activation.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
Bambu Farm Manager Server is the background service of the Farm Manager suite. It discovers printers on the local network, coordinates communication, and orchestrates a shared job queue so multiple devices can be driven efficiently from one place.

### Features
- Central job queue and scheduling across multiple printers
- Reliable LAN communication and status reporting
- Batch operations (send, reorder, pause/resume, cancel) for farm workflows
- Local-first operation after initial activation (privacy-friendly)
- Basic logging and device availability checks

### What this package does
- Installs the **Farm Manager Server** for Windows using the official installer (silent "/S")
- Suitable for unattended/automated deployments and AU-based updates

### Compatibility and requirements
- Windows 10/11 (per vendor support)
- Administrator privileges may be required in some environments

### Post-install verification
- Start “Farm Manager Server” and confirm printers on the same LAN are discovered and report status in the client.

